content.description: Just when you are in the choss filled Wrangell's, life finds a way to produce a crack climb in front of your eyes. Lie-back to stem / chimney technique.
content.protection: Mountaineering boots, rain gear, sense of adventure.
content.location: Obvious crack goes from one foot to three foot wide.

pathTokens: Wrangell, St. Elias, University and Fairweather Ranges

content.description:
A large 35’ x 15’ erratic that somehow found its way into the river valley and cracked open. The boulder is made of conglomerate material and has a one foot crack to a 3 ft crack. There exists potential for a fun jug haul on the downriver side of the boulder for next visitor's first ascent.

 To descend, walk off the back the rock diagonally opposite of the crack on river-side.
